CHANGELOG — Do It List

Plain text. Append-only. Chronological (oldest first). Records scope, requirement, and doc-structure changes — not git commit history.

2026-05-05  M01-BaseApp scaffold landed; project pushed to https://github.com/n8bar/DoItList as a public MIT repo.
2026-05-05  Established doc hierarchy: ProductSpec.md as master spec, PLAN.md as master action list, CLAUDE.md as always-loaded primer above the spec/action split. Defined the "stay at your altitude" rule.
2026-05-06  Migrated milestone docs into docs/milestones/<milestone>/ subfolders. Codified the action-list hierarchy (Milestone -> Arc -> Worklist -> Item -> Subitem), dotted reference notation (m##.NN.NN.NN.NN), and branch naming (M##-<slug> + semantic prefixes).
2026-05-06  Added baseline ancillary docs: BACKLOG.md, FINDINGS.md, UX_GUARDRAILS.md, CHANGELOG.log. Added milestone-deadline convention (target dates required, approximate flags allowed).
2026-05-06  M02-UX-Overhaul scoped (target 2026-05-15). Two arcs: m02.01 UX guardrails audit & alignment; m02.02 design refinements (theme toggle, progress underbar, completion checkbox + cascade-confirm, collapsible children, inline description with em dash, project header bar, add-subtask signifier rework). Task `status` field removed from UI; schema column retained for possible later revival.
2026-05-06  Slimmed docs/PLAN.md by extracting Doc Roles and conventions (numbering, doc layout, specs vs. actions, deadlines) into new docs/README.md. Old PLAN §4 Branches and §5 Repo deleted as duplicates of CLAUDE.md. CLAUDE.md gained a pointer line directing agents to docs/README.md when adding docs or making structural decisions.
2026-05-07  Updated CLAUDE.md to current conventions: spec-first rule now points at docs/milestones/m##-<slug>/m##-<slug>.md (was docs/m##-*.md); branch naming switched from claude/<task> to M##-<slug> + semantic prefixes (fix/, chore/, docs/, spike/). Removed the "once the remote is set up" qualifier on the canonical-main rule since the remote is set up.
2026-05-07  Renamed Project to Orchard in ProductSpec.md vocabulary (cascades to Orchard member, "Multiple users may open the same Orchard"). Added Visual Metaphor section reserving tree/branch/leaf icons for Lists/parent-tasks/leaf-tasks and reserving Fruit/Crop names for a future goals concept. The code/schema rename to Orchard is a separate chore awaiting approval.
2026-05-07  Tightened docs/README.md numbering conventions: Arc headings use local number only (`### 1 — <name>`), and items must not prefix themselves with their own dotted reference. M02 doc reformatted to comply. Mirrored to core-doc-scaffold.
2026-05-07  Renamed Project to Orchard everywhere — DB (tables, columns, FK constraints, indexes, sequences via reversible rename migration), code (DoIt.Projects -> DoIt.Orchards module + schemas + function names + routes + PubSub topics), tests, M01 spec (retroactive), CLAUDE.md vocabulary, README.md. No data dropped. Three-commit chore branch: chore/orchard-rename.
2026-05-07  Tightened checkbox convention in docs/README.md: checkboxes mark actionable items only, never action-list titles or headings (Milestone, Arc, Worklist). Mirrored to core-doc-scaffold. Fixed misleading copy on the orchards index that implied 1:1 between Orchard and tree (now: Orchard holds multiple Lists; each List is a tree).
2026-05-07  Renamed Orchard to Initiative everywhere — second rename in two days, after deciding Orchard didn't communicate "purposeful work toward a goal". DB rename migration is reversible; no data dropped. Code, schemas, routes, tests, M01 spec (retroactive), M02 spec (Initiative-level progress underbar, item 9 grove-icon addition), ProductSpec metaphor section, CLAUDE.md vocabulary, README.md, PLAN.md M01+M02 rows. Three-commit chore branch: chore/initiative-rename. Botanical icon metaphor preserved at the visual layer (Lucide trees/tree/branch/leaf for Initiative/List/parent-task/leaf-task).
2026-05-08  Tightened FINDINGS.md conventions. Rule 2 status definitions now point at rule 6 for promotion's precise meaning. Rule 6 sharpens promoted as "an unchecked action item owns the fix at the moment of status change". New rule 7: pre-scoped refinements already covered by an upcoming milestone/arc are not findings. New rule 8: two paths to a fix — promote (action list owns the fix) or fix inline (the finding owns the fix via `**[ ] fix:**` ↔ `**[x] fix:**` checkbox); inline can escalate to promotion if scope grows. Mirrored to core-doc-scaffold.
2026-05-08  Deleted docs/FINDINGS.md. Issues and bugs now tracked in GitHub Issues. The doc-as-code findings convention we built up today (rules 1-8) is preserved in git history at commit 1419c49 if we ever want to restore it. docs/README.md updated to drop FINDINGS from § Other level-1 docs. Scaffold also dropping FINDINGS.md from its default (separate commit there).
2026-05-08  Added Working Style rule to CLAUDE.md: "Bug fixes are fair game on any branch if they're documented first." Preserves the doc-before-fix discipline that the inline-fix path of the deleted FINDINGS.md used to encode, in a medium-agnostic form (issue, commit message, etc.).
2026-05-08  Finalized M02 spec. Arc 1 reshaped from "audit + log findings + resolve" (3 items) into "bring M01 to spec" (2 items): (1) add project-specific UX rules to UX_GUARDRAILS.md, (2) audit M01 baseline and fix gaps not already covered by Arc 2 items. Arc 2's items are responsible for following UX_GUARDRAILS in their own implementations — no separate verification step. Arc 2 gained item 2 (Edit Initiative metadata via right-rail panel) at position 2; original items 2-9 renumbered as 3-10; cross-references updated. UX_GUARDRAILS.md gained the two project-specific rules (A.1 default-hidden attributes; B.1 no layout shift on collapse/theme). All FINDINGS.md references removed from the spec.
2026-05-08  M02 Arc 1 complete. Item 1 (UX rules) shipped with spec finalization. Item 2 (M01 baseline gap-closure): motion-reduce on transitions, aria-labels on member-email/role/comment inputs, phx-disable-with on Create/Add/Post buttons, error flashes now include changeset details via new summarize_errors helper in InitiativeShowLive. 28/28 tests pass. Other baseline gaps deferred to Arc 2 items that touch the same code (theme toggle owns dark mode + contrast; signifier rework owns the + button label; row layout owns form rework + most touch targets).
2026-05-08  M02 Arc 2 item 1 (theme toggle) initial pass shipped: three-state control (System/Light/Dark) with Heroicon glyphs, server-side persistence on users.theme (new column; nullable; "system" stored as nil so DaisyUI's prefersdark handles it), client-side localStorage sync via existing root.html.heex JS (extended to handle both click-target and push_event payload shapes), global on_mount hook in DoItWeb.UserAuth attaches a handle_event for "set_theme" so any LiveView persists without reimplementing. Dark variants applied to body, header, initiative index, initiative show, and home page. Polish to follow as gaps surface in dogfooding.
2026-05-08  M02 Arc 2 item 2 (Initiative rename UI) shipped: static pencil signifier next to the Initiative h1 (no hover dependency; mobile-friendly); h1 itself is also clickable. Right-rail panel becomes polymorphic — clicking edit_initiative flips the panel to "Initiative details" with name + description fields; clicking a task flips back to "Task details". The two panels are mutually exclusive, enforced by the LiveView's selection assigns. New Initiatives.update_initiative/2; new initiative_editor LiveView component. Auto-save on phx-change via phx-debounce (matches Task editor pattern).
2026-05-08  M02 Arc 2 item 3 (full-width progress underbar) shipped. Replaced the inline percentage text + small fixed-width progress widget with a thin underbar pinned to the bottom edge of each task row (full row width less a small horizontal margin). Driven by a `--progress` CSS custom property so progress updates don't shift layout. Same treatment at every depth in the tree. Underbar carries role="progressbar" + aria-valuenow + aria-label so screen readers get the value (and a hover title for sighted users since the percentage text is no longer visible inline). Same commit also added aria-label to the + add-subtask button (small, scope-relevant).
2026-05-08  M02 Arc 2 item 4 (completion checkbox) shipped. Each task row gains a checkbox immediately before the title. Leaf-task click toggles progress 0 ↔ 100 (via new Tasks.toggle_complete/2). Parent-task click opens a browser confirm dialog (via data-confirm); on confirm, cascade marks the task and every descendant done (new Tasks.cascade_complete/2; uses existing update_task per node so each gets activity events and ancestor progress recompute, wrapped in a single transaction). Checkbox button is keyboard-operable, has aria-pressed + aria-label, and uses motion-reduce for the transition. Also fixed a strict-and BadBooleanError on the polymorphic right-rail :if guard from item 2 (`@selected_task_id and not ...` → `@selected_task_id && not ...`).
2026-05-08  M02 Arc 2 item 5 (collapsible children) shipped. Tasks with children get a chevron toggle button (visually distinct from the + add-subtask signifier — chevron rotates -90° when collapsed via aria-[expanded=false] Tailwind variant; transitions respect motion-reduce). Per-task collapsed state persists in localStorage only, keyed by `phx:collapse:<initiative_id>:<task_id>`. Default state on first view is expanded. Implementation is a colocated phx-hook on the toggle button that toggles a `hidden` class on the children `<ul>` (id="children-#{task.id}"); LiveView re-renders preserve the state via the hook's `updated()` callback. Roll-up calculation is unaffected — only visual children are hidden.
2026-05-08  M02 Arc 2 item 6 (task row layout) shipped. Single-line row in spec order: chevron · checkbox · botanical-icon-placeholder · title · attribute-chips (weight ≠ 1, priority ≠ normal, assignee set — per UX_GUARDRAILS A.1) · em-dash + description (faded, truncated with ellipsis, hidden below sm breakpoint) · + add-subtask · progress underbar. Whole row is now phx-click="select_task" so clicking anywhere outside the inner buttons opens detail; inner buttons use onclick="event.stopPropagation()" to prevent double-fire. The botanical icon slot uses Heroicon stand-ins until item 10 swaps in Lucide.
2026-05-08  M02 Arc 2 items 7-10 shipped. Item 7: Initiative-level progress underbar (equal-weighted average of root-task progress) pinned to bottom of the Initiative header. Item 8: add-subtask signifier reworked from a dinky inline `+` to a labeled pill (icon + "Subtask" text on >=sm; icon-only on narrow), min-h-11 min-w-11 for the 44×44 touch-target rule. Item 9: removed the Status select and Mark-done/Reopen button from the Task editor; activity log filters out kind:status_changed entries; Tasks.record_diff_events no longer records status_changed. Item 10: botanical icon set added via new <.botanical_icon> component in CoreComponents (Lucide-source SVG, MIT) — grove on Initiatives (header + list cards), tree on Lists (depth 0), branch on parent tasks (depth > 0 with children), leaf on leaf tasks (depth > 0 without children). M02 implementation complete; visual review of light + dark modes and M01 regression check pending in browser.
2026-05-09  Casual-testing pass on items 1-10 surfaced six refinements that landed in the M02 spec as Arc 2 items 11-16: (11) click-h1 inline-edit + small ellipses button to open the polymorphic Details panel; pencil from original item 2 removed; (12) centered numerical percentage text inside progress underbars with high-contrast text shadow; (13) drop the "Lists & tasks" h2 and give List titles depth-based larger/bolder treatment; (14) "+ New List" button in the Initiative h1 row and rename row-level pill from "+ Subtask" to "+ New Task"; (15) tree icon green / branch icon brown / leaf icon green, plus a custom actual-tree-branch SVG replacing Lucide's git-branch graph; (16) mobile-friendly Details flyout — below `lg:` the right-rail (Members + Details) becomes a fixed overlay sliding from the right with a backdrop, dismissable via tap-outside or close button. Acceptance criteria updated to count sixteen items.
2026-05-09  Continued casual-testing pass on items 1-16 surfaced ten more refinements that landed in the M02 spec as Arc 2 items 17-26: (17) fixed-height flex-column layout — `<body>` is `h-screen flex flex-col`, `<header>` is `flex-none`, `<main>` is `flex-1 overflow-y-auto`, header always visible because only `<main>` scrolls (NO `position: sticky`); (18) Initiatives nav moved left of the theme toggle and visually separated; (19) borders on all add-buttons; (20) branch icon redrawn as a brown branch with 2-3 small green leaves; (21) clicking a selected task deselects it (row click is a toggle); (22) bold green text styling on add-buttons; (23) password show/hide eyeball on login + register; (24) drop weight input from new-task line (default 1; edit via Details); (25) sibling-creation split-button on `+ New Task` (main click = child, `▶` menu = sibling); (26) Initiatives index sorts own-first and shows role badge (`owner`/`editor`/`viewer`) per card. Acceptance criteria updated to count twenty-six items. Implementation pending owner approval.
2026-05-09  Split M02 into per-arc files per docs/README.md § 2.3. New: `m02.01-bring-to-spec.md` (Arc 1, 2 items, complete) and `m02.02-design-refinements.md` (Arc 2, 26 items — 16 done + 10 pending approval). Milestone doc `m02-ux-overhaul.md` slimmed to a rollup: Goal, Preconditions, Arcs table linking to the arc files, Non-Goals, Acceptance Criteria, Branch. No item content changed; this is a doc-structure refactor only. Future Arcs 3 (drag-and-drop) and 4 (Collaborators wide-rail) will get their own files when approved.
