2026-05-09  M02 Arc 2 items 17-26 shipped (Arc 2 complete). (17) Body becomes h-screen flex flex-col; header is flex-none; main is flex-1 overflow-y-auto. Header always visible because only main scrolls — no sticky positioning. (18) Initiatives nav moved to the left of the theme toggle in the header, with thin vertical dividers separating Initiatives / theme / user-name+logout. (19+22) New List, New Task (row), and Add Member buttons unified into a green-bordered, bold-green pill family. The Add Member button gained a + icon and label "Add Member" to match. (20) Branch botanical icon redrawn — currentColor brown stroke for the branch with an inner <g class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400" fill="currentColor"> of three small rotated ellipses for leaves. (21) select_task event now toggles: clicking the currently-selected task clears selection and closes the Details panel. (23) New `password`-type clause on the `<.input>` core component renders the input wrapped with a Heroicon eye / eye-slash button; client-side `Hooks.PasswordToggle` swaps input.type and the visible icon. Applies to login + register out of the box. (24) Removed the inline weight number input from the new-task form; create_task already defaults missing weight to 1.0 server-side. (25) Row-level + New Task pill becomes a split-button: main click adds a child of THIS task (unchanged); a `▶` triangle button opens a small dropdown with "+ New Task at this level" — new show_add_sibling event looks up the clicked task's parent_id and sets add_task_for to it (or :root if the clicked task is already a root). Dropdown is JS.toggle on a positioned panel. (26) Initiatives.list_visible_initiatives now selects each Initiative with the user's role into a new virtual Initiative.my_role field; results are ordered owner-first (CASE-fragment) then by updated_at desc. The index card shows my_role as a small role-colored badge (emerald for owner, blue for editor, zinc for viewer). create_initiative path manually sets my_role: "owner" on the just-inserted struct so stream_insert at the top renders correctly. All 28 tests pass.
